1
00:00:03,837 --> 00:00:07,796
This is the story
of 2 girls- Anju and Manju,...

2
00:00:08,842 --> 00:00:13,802
..who were born in this palatial
mansion but never enjoyed it.

3
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:19,808
When Manju was 6 months old,
her maid kidnapped her.

4
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,823
It is rumoured that
the maid was mentally unstable.

5
00:00:41,374 --> 00:00:45,879
- Master! Master! -The owners
took this loss to heart...

6
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:50,383
... and called Tribhuvan
from the village...

7
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:52,351
... to look after the property.

8
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:54,888
As soon as Tribhuvan arrived...

9
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:57,857
... plots started
floating around the mansion...

10
00:00:58,391 --> 00:01:02,851
...cause he wanted his brother's
immeasurable wealth for himself.

11
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:06,866
When Anju was ten...

12
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,871
... her parents died
in a car accident.

13
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:16,864
But people say that accident
had been caused to happen.

14
00:01:17,410 --> 00:01:21,915
But nothing was proved. After
Tribhuvan's wife's death...

15
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:26,375
... his sister-in-law,
Amba came to leave his son.

16
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:30,389
Amba came but never went back.

17
00:01:31,424 --> 00:01:33,892
It's said that Tribhuvan
and Amba had an affair.

18
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:39,887
One day Tribhuvan
tried to kill Anju too.

19
00:01:40,433 --> 00:01:42,435
But the cunning Amba stopped him.

20
00:01:42,435 --> 00:01:45,404
As the property would
then have gone to the trust.

21
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:50,443
Tribhuvan swallowed his anger...

22
00:01:50,443 --> 00:01:54,402
... and poor Anju
had to pay the price.

23
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:12,420
No! I don't want it.

24
00:02:36,152 --> 00:02:47,887
Mr.India and WWW.LAPACHE.INFO
PRESENT :

25
00:02:55,744 --> 00:02:59,992
CHAALBAAZ

26
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:14,087
- Why are you late? - Today is
her parents' death anniversary...

27
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,554
... so she was shedding tears.

28
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:19,092
Today is my brother and
his wife's death anniversary...

29
00:04:19,092 --> 00:04:20,593
... and no-one told me!

30
00:04:20,593 --> 00:04:26,099
This is disloyalty that the
brother who looked after me...

31
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:28,067
... I forgot
his death anniversary!

32
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:32,605
I' m not worthy of pardon. I
should be punished for my crime.

33
00:04:32,605 --> 00:04:37,065
- Anju, what's my punishment?
- What are you saying, Uncle?

34
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:43,116
I... was crying
because of my helplessness...

35
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:47,576
Who made you helpless?
Did you, Amba?

36
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:52,080
How could I dare do that?
I' m a guest in this house.

37
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,127
Anju is the
mistress of this house.

38
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:57,585
Yes, her
wish will come true now.

39
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:02,090
Anju, what do you want?
Tell me, my child.

40
00:05:04,637 --> 00:05:14,103
I' ll offer flowers worth Rs.5/-
to the temple in their name.

41
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:20,608
Only worth Rs.5? For my
honourable brother and his wife?

42
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:24,657
Absolutely not! Buy all
the flowers from all the shops.

43
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:28,161
10-ay Anju, in memory of
her parents, will distribute...

44
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:33,121
... clothes and
sweets to poor children.

45
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:38,171
- Really? - Yes, child.
- But the money?

46
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:43,676
Don't you dare talk of money.
Here dear, keep this money.

47
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:48,136
- Distribute it. - No.
- Take it, my dear.

48
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:57,156
You must be crazy
to think I'd give you money.

49
00:05:57,690 --> 00:06:06,155
One only sheds tears for the
dead. Come on, to the bank.

50
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:15,208
Come on and no excuses at the
bank. I' m fed up of your tears.

51
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:17,176
Keep this. Go.

52
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:23,171
- Miss Anju, here's your money.
- Give it to me.

53
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:27,220
Times are bad these days.

54
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:30,189
Carrying money
is quite dangerous.

55
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:33,192
We' re in a hurry.
We take leave.

56
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:35,228
What's the hurry?

57
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:41,734
- Have a cup of tea.
- Today is my brother's death...

58
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:45,693
...anniversary. Anju has to dole
out clothes & sweets to the poor.

59
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,241
We have lots of work.
So we must take leave.

60
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:52,701
- You' re forgetting something.
- No, I've taken the money.

61
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:57,706
- Anju has forgotting to sign.
- Oh!

62
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:00,719
Take.

63
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:08,727
Cap!

64
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:19,738
Sign.

65
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:32,741
- Who gave this money?
- To buy flowers, Dadu gave it.

66
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:37,756
Dayal, come here.

67
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:46,765
Dayal take off my shoes.

68
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:55,263
Your fingers have grown
old serving this family, Dayal.

69
00:07:55,808 --> 00:07:57,776
I' m proud of this fact, master.

70
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:04,817
Who does this much to
earn one's livelihood?

71
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:07,786
I' m slave to
your command, master.

72
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:11,290
Why did you give Anju
money against my wishes?

73
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,301
- Want money?
- Don't beat Dadu.

74
00:08:23,836 --> 00:08:26,839
Want to
celebrate their anniversary?

75
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:33,346
- Only five rupees. - What?
- He only gave me five rupees.

76
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,813
How dare you speak back!

77
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:41,309
It's very important for you
to obey me Dayal. - Yes sir.

78
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:49,817
Hold this! Hold. Hold it.

79
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:56,824
Celebrate their
anniversary go on!

80
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:00,839
Have you gone mad? If she dies
we' ll be on the road. - But...

81
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:07,380
Can't you wait?
Spoiling matters.

82
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,382
Still standing here!

83
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:15,343
Go do your work
It's only a little blood!

84
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:24,351
Sister, if something happens
to you, what' ll I do?

85
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:31,359
Yes Raju, I have to
live. For you, I must.

86
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:35,863
I have nobody else but you!

87
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:44,382
All this should be clean by the
time we return, understand?

88
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:48,876
Or l' ll make you wash
the floor with your tears.

89
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:52,891
She's putting on weight!
Cut out one meal from her diet.

90
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:56,895
Everything should be clean,
understand...

91
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:01,388
Stop crying and smile for me.

92
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:07,440
Please sister.
Okay whom shall I imitate?

93
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,907
Shall I mimic Papa?

94
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:15,402
She's put on weight,
Cut out one meal from her diet.

95
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:26,925
Sis, I want to get married.

96
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:31,930
Strange, you' re not at all
interested in my personal life.

97
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,436
Friend, sis doesn't want
to hear, so l' ll tell you.

98
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:43,476
If I get married,
she' ll get some respite.

99
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:46,445
I've seen a girl also.
She studies in my class.

100
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:51,439
She's unmarried so far. She
helped me with my spellings once.

101
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:54,987
But her nose is always running!

102
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:58,946
She' ll bring lots of
chocolates in her dowry.

103
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:03,451
I would've refused but its a
matter of all those chocolates.

104
00:11:03,996 --> 00:11:08,456
- Sis, talk to her folks.
- Crazy guy, stop it!

105
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:13,461
I haven't seen
you dance for ages.

106
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:15,474
No.

107
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:20,012
You know what' ll happen
if they catch me dancing.

108
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:23,470
Your face glows with
happiness when you dance.

109
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:24,983
No.

110
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:33,601
- We did hear some music here.
- Even I heard it.

111
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:40,653
- Yes, sir.
- Who was dancing here?

112
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:46,659
Dancing? God knows.
Anju was cleaning this place.

113
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:52,665
Raju must the playing somewhere
and at my age, I can't dance.

114
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:55,634
- Answer to the point, go.
- Alright.

115
00:13:57,169 --> 00:13:59,637
I've called important
people for my birthday.

116
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:02,140
Keep an eye on Anju.

117
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:04,142
You've said it
and Amba has heard it.

118
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:07,646
- You relax. - Aren't you
forgetting something?

119
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:10,649
- What?
- Nothing.

120
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:15,643
Oh! Many happy
returns of the day.

121
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:19,658
By the way,
how old one you today?

122
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:22,661
Have I ever asked you your age?

123
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:33,205
Happy birthday. So how many
winters have you seen go by?

124
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:36,709
- l' m a little boy still.
- Where's Anju? I don't see her.

125
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,711
She must be busy.

126
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:42,715
I keep telling her there's
no need for her to work.

127
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:47,720
But she loves to
do everything herself.

128
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:52,725
- And where's Suraj?
- I don't understand him at all.

129
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:57,685
All kids return home by 10 but
his night begins only after 10.

130
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:03,736
Have you planned for some
dance or its just cake and out?

131
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:06,705
Wait a minute and watch,
Mr.Vishwanath.

132
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:13,701
Friends, thank you for
joining me in my joy.

133
00:15:14,246 --> 00:15:19,251
You've always abused
me for my miserliness.

134
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:25,713
But today your abuses will be
drowned by applause. Clap!

135
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:54,242
Anju, what' re you doing
here alone. Come, join in, come.

136
00:18:42,454 --> 00:18:45,912
How dare she slap
you before other's Tribhuvan!

137
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:54,967
You must take charge or
things will go out of hand.

138
00:18:54,967 --> 00:19:01,930
I won't spare her,my whip hasn't
tasted her blood for some time.

139
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:22,950
Dance! Let me see
how much you' ll dance today.

140
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:26,965
Today l' ll make you dance
to your hearts content.

141
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:44,482
No! Don't beat me.

142
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:48,520
Get up!

143
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,489
Beat me!
Yopu will beat me?

144
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:53,992
Dance! You love to dance!

145
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:59,486
I' ll show you such a dance that
you' ll forget your own dance.

146
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:07,494
You've danced to music, now
dance to the tune of my whip.

147
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:17,049
If I let go of you,
you' ll fall and become lame.

148
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:20,052
And you won't be able to
dance anymore! Shall I let go?

149
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:24,011
- No.
- No, okay I won't let you fall.

150
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:38,036
Got hurt? Broke your leg?

151
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:47,535
Now we' ll make dear Anju stand &
check whether her leg is broken.

152
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:51,049
It hasn't broken. Then
now it' ll break!

153
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:59,091
You' ll hit me!
On my birthday!

154
00:20:59,091 --> 00:21:04,096
You will humiliate me in
everyone's presence?

155
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:07,065
Master! Stop it! Have mercy!

156
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:14,562
Forgive Anju, sir!
She' ll never dance.

157
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:19,111
Explain to, her that if she ever
dances again,...

158
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:22,569
... she wont have feet left!

159
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:26,083
She won't dance again.

160
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:36,583
Get up child.

161
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:45,093
Get me poison, Dadu.
I want to die, Dadu.

162
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:48,106
Why doesn't death come to me?

163
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:53,099
I cannot take this anymore.

164
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:59,106
Have patience child
and trust in God.

165
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:02,119
Remember my child.

166
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:08,660
Whoever gave that whip in
Tribhuvan's hand, also gave...

167
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:13,620
... somebody else the
power to snatch it from him.

168
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:20,137
Manju is my name, what?

169
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:39,191
- Sorry, Manju bai.
- Me, bai, a courtesan.

170
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,193
You called me a super stage
artiste, a courtesan?

171
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:43,161
I didn't, my boss did.

172
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:47,199
Will you pay me or not.

173
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:53,205
I danced and performed
a whole show for you.

174
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:55,673
Didn't you tell her what I said?

175
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,212
What did he say?

176
00:23:00,212 --> 00:23:03,670
He said you should come for
dinner to claim your money.

177
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:14,191
Take care of this girl.

178
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:24,191
Brother, you?
I...I was simply joking!

179
00:23:24,736 --> 00:23:33,201
Doesn't matter, l' ll take
my money later. Bye, Tata.

180
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:38,750
Jaggu, things are
beyond my control now.

181
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:41,218
I won't get involved
in your problems.

182
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:57,269
Sir, you banged into my car.
Please pay up for the damage.

183
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:59,237
You want money, here take this.

184
00:25:47,879 --> 00:25:50,347
Jaggu, sir.
I was just paying up.

185
00:25:57,389 --> 00:26:00,358
Take it. Rs 60/- for taxi damage.

186
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:03,360
You keep the rest.
He dented my cab.

187
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:11,358
- What?
- Dirty, dirty, chhee!

188
00:26:11,903 --> 00:26:14,406
You speak as if it's yours.
Come on, put down the meter.

189
00:26:14,406 --> 00:26:17,409
- This cab is booked.
- l' ll pay the full fare.

190
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:21,413
- You' ll pay?
- Look, don't act smart.

191
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:22,914
There are plenty of cabs in town.

192
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:24,916
Then go with somebody else.

193
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:27,919
If I go elsewhere,
what' ll happen to your meter?

194
00:26:27,919 --> 00:26:29,887
You've a big actress,
come on, sit.

195
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:32,890
Red Fairy!

196
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:46,438
- Here take five rupees.
- Five rupees?

197
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:48,406
But the meter
shows twelve rupees.

198
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:54,446
- We used fuel worth five bucks.
- Is the cab your pop's?

199
00:26:54,446 --> 00:26:57,904
- Don't reach my Dad.
- Okay, okay.

200
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:01,953
- Keep these five
rupees for your dowry. - Okay.

201
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:07,414
Marry a nice chap. These daily
fights are not meant for you.

202
00:27:07,959 --> 00:27:13,420
Soon you' ll see me as
an all lndia star!

203
00:27:15,967 --> 00:27:17,469
Have you ever seen
yourself in a mirror?

204
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:19,471
Get married before its late.

205
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:21,973
Or you' ll be left beating
the drums at a brothel.

206
00:27:21,973 --> 00:27:25,431
Or you' ll and up as some one's
mistress.Now get lost l' m going.

207
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:30,437
Stupid girl! Wears rented
clothes and dreams of stardom!

208
00:27:32,984 --> 00:27:39,446
My name is Chinchinchu,the night
is moonlight, you and me...

209
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:45,497
My buffalo has become
thin feeding you her milk.

210
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:49,501
I've got blisters on my hands,
washing your clothes.Pay me now.

211
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:52,470
You ate my salt and now want
to gulp down our money too.

212
00:27:55,507 --> 00:28:00,467
You found this day to
come to claim your money.

213
00:28:01,513 --> 00:28:03,481
Why Manju? What happened?

214
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:09,521
What is left to happen now?
My mom!

215
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:14,526
- What happened to her? - The
same that happened to Dilip...

216
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:17,984
... Kumar in Devdas and
Rajesh Khanna in Anand.

217
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:22,489
- Super hit!
- No, cancer.

218
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:29,996
When my mom is no more,
why should I live?

219
00:28:31,042 --> 00:28:35,046
I too will die! Your milk...

220
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:39,050
- Not mine, my buffalo's.
- Whatever, your clothes.

221
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:43,009
Everything will
be dust in the end.

222
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:47,058
We came and will
return empty handed.

223
00:28:47,058 --> 00:28:49,526
Be it a king or a beggar,
a Manju or a Bihari.

224
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:53,030
- Finally what's in your lives?
- What?

225
00:28:54,065 --> 00:28:58,525
Nothing but a coffin and
2 feet of earth.

226
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:01,538
There's nothing in
this game, nothing.

227
00:29:02,073 --> 00:29:05,531
It's a two day game with income
tax problems in between.

228
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:09,581
When the heart is
broken, why live?

229
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:12,550
I am leaving.
Where's my house? Where?

230
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:17,088
Don't Manju! Are we dead?
In bad times we' ll help you.

231
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:23,049
No brother I've bothered
you enough already. No more now.

232
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:26,097
At the most people' ll
say she could pay...

